    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: SRGAP2A and the emergence of the human-specific paralogs SRGAP2B and SRGAP2C.\n\nAuthors analyzed the ability of human-SRGAP2B and -SRGAP2C to regulate excitatory synaptic density and maturation in mice by quantifying spine density and spine head size of apical oblique dendrites at juvenile (P21 - Fig. 3) and adult (>P65 - Fig. 4) stages of layer 2/3 cortical pyramidal neurons.\n\nFigure 3c, 4b: expression of SRGAP2B induced an increase in dendritic spine density at P21 and a minor increase at P65 (note; effect was stronger in SRGAP2C for both time points).\n\nFigure 3d, 4c: expression of SRGAP2B induced a decrease in dendritic spine head size at P21 (note; effect was stronger in SRGAP2C) but no significant differences at P65.. Experimental description: From M&M:\n\"Cortical neurons were ex utero electroporated (EUE) by injecting endotoxin-free DNA (500 ng/ul for cell filler and 750 ng/ul for each fusion protein construct) into the lateral ventricle of E15.5 mouse embryos and ...\"\n\n\"Plasmids for expression of SRGAP2A-RFP, SRGAP2C-RFP, SRGAP2B-RFP, F-BARΔ49 -RFP, 5R-RFP, F-BARx-RFP, and myristoylated-Venus (mVenus), were as previously described\" (PMID: 22559944).",
